events.name: GDG DevFest Karachi 2017
events.description:
Google Developer Groups(GDG) DevFests are large, community-run events that can offer speaker sessions across multiple product areas, all-day hack-a-thons, code labs, and more. Each DevFest is tailored by the GDG as per the needs of the local community.

Please register yourself here.

GDG DevFest Karachi 2017 is being organized by GDG Kolachi and will be held on November 18-19, 2017 at NED University of Engineering and Technology, Karachi. Last year GDG Kolachi's DevFest had 300+ participants that consisted of motivated students, experienced professionals, designers, quality assurance engineers and entrepreneurs. You can find more about the last year’s DevFest here. This time we plan on making it bigger and better!

GDG DevFest Karachi 2017 is a free event and only has a limited number of seats. If you are shortlisted, you will receive a confirmation email and SMS. You can also check the status of your application on this web app as well. Once you are shortlisted you will be asked to confirm your registration on this portal, once you have confirmed your registration, then you can access your free ticket which you have to bring along with yourself at the DevFest. We highly recommend all professionals/students to please talk to your employer/professor for a leave before registering for the GDG DevFest Karachi 2017, as your attendance is what lights up the conference and we don't want to miss you!

You can find more about GDG Kolachi and GDG DevFest Karachi 2017 here:

<a>https://www.facebook.com/GDGKolachi/</a>;

<a>https://twitter.com/GDGKolachi/</a>;

If you have any questions, please write to us @ [masked]

events.name: Workshop: Introduction to Docker and Kubernetes
events.description:
• What we'll do
Docker and Kubernetes are changing the way we configure our server and deployments. Be it your local environment setup, your CI pipeline or your massive production cluster - these two technologies make it easier and more manageable to setup and deploy. This hands on workshop is all about what these technologies are about and how they will help you setup and deploy your next product!

This workshop will be delivered by Technical Lead at 10Pearls Mohammad Umair Ali Khan and Technical Lead at Recurship and Google Developer Expert Mashhood Rastgar who are both using these technologies in their respective organizations.

• What to bring
Laptops

• Important to know
Registration required!

Limited seats. This is a free event.

events.name: Mobile Sites Certification - FAST

venue.name: FAST - National University of Computer and Emerging Sciences
venue.address_1: ST-4 Sector 17-D, On National Highway, Karachi

events.description:
• What we'll do
People often find it easier to learn together rather than do pure self study. ACM – NUCES with collaboration of GDG Kolachi is going to organize a one day event for FASTIANS in order to equip them with the skills required to build next generation mobile sites, and get certified.

The event will be approximately 3-4 hours long. During the first half of the event, Pakistan's first technical Google Developer Expert along with other industry experts will introduce concepts related to mobile sites and the study materials necessary to pass the certification. After that, students will attempt multiple choice questions based exam, and instantly get certified. Google Developer Groups (GDGs) are for developers who are interested in Google's developer technology; everything from the Android, Chrome, Drive and Google Cloud platforms, to product APIs like the Cast API, Maps API, and Youtube API. The local chapter of Google Developers Group in Karachi is called GDG Kolachi, you can find more about their activity here: https://www.facebook.com/GDGKolachi/
https://www.facebook.com/acmnuces/inbox/

Register Yourself Now at:
https://goo.gl/forms/OqPHBOLDpeRqC74M2
Registration Deadline 9th February!!!

*Limited Seats Available
**Only For Seniors & Juniors of FAST-NUCES

events.name: GDG Kolachi : Cloud Study Jam

venue.name: NED University of Engineering and Technology

events.description:
Join GDG Kolachi for a study jam session on deploying applications, powered by Qwiklabs!

Qwiklabs has step by step walkthroughs which guides you from start to finish. This study jam is a self paced, stress free and fun session on deploying applications on GCP. We will also have trainers and facilitators to help you out with the material and GCP access. You will be given Qwiklabs credits on the day of event to complete "Deploying Application" Quest.

Successfully completing the labs will earn you a Google Cloud Platform Badge which you can share and can put on your resume.

Harris Solangi, Technology and Innovation Head, AzCorp Entertainment
Sami Haroon Khan, Software and Cloud Engineer, Oraan
